GLOBAL PROSPERITY OPEN LICENSE (GPOL)
Version 1.0 | Effective Date: February 2026

1. THE FOUNDATION'S MANDATE

1.1 The Public Good. This License is issued by The Omega Institute
(the "Foundation") to facilitate the creation of a "Global Innovation
Commons."

1.2 Creator Endowment. The Foundation serves as a fiduciary agent for
Creators, collecting "Prosperity Contributions" from highly successful
entities to reinvest in the original Developers and the broader
technology ecosystem.

2. DEFINITIONS

2.1 "Threshold" means a financial milestone defined as 0.01% of the
Global Gross Domestic Product (GDP) as officially published by the
World Bank (or successor intergovernmental body) for the immediately
preceding fiscal year.

2.2 "Gross Revenue" means all income derived by a Licensee and its
Affiliates, as reflected in audited financial statements, tax filings,
or mandatory public disclosures (e.g., SEC Form 10-K).

2.3 "Creators" means the individual developers or entities who
contribute original source code to the Foundation's repo under this
License.

3. GRANT OF LICENSE & DEFERRED ROYALTY

3.1 Irrevocable Grant. Subject to Section 3.2, the Foundation hereby
grants you a worldwide, royalty-free, non-exclusive license to use,
reproduce, modify, and distribute the Software.

3.2 The Prosperity Covenant. As a condition of this License, you agree
that if and when your Gross Revenue meets or exceeds the Threshold, you
shall be legally bound to pay a "Prosperity Contribution" to the
Foundation equal to 1% of your annual Net Profit.

3.3 Deferred Maturity. The parties acknowledge that the Software may
contribute to your commercial success over a multi-decade horizon. Your
obligation to contribute remains binding regardless of the duration of
time elapsed between the initial adoption of the code and the crossing
of the Threshold.

4. TRANSPARENCY & VERIFICATION

4.1 Public Data Reliance. For Licensees that are publicly traded or
otherwise required to publish financial results, the Foundation shall
rely on such Public Records to determine whether the Threshold has been
met.

4.2 Constructive Notice. You acknowledge that reaching the Threshold
constitutes a "trigger event," and you waive any defense based on the
Foundation's failure to send a manual invoice, provided the Threshold
status is ascertainable from public financial data.

5. INTELLECTUAL PROPERTY & ATTRIBUTION

5.1 Retained Rights. Creators retain copyright in their original
contributions but grant the Foundation the right to license such works
under these GPOL terms.

5.2 Integrity of Attribution. You must retain all copyright, patent,
and attribution notices in the source code. You may not claim "sole
inventorship" over the Foundation's core library in any patent
application.

6. TERMINATION & REVERSION

6.1 Automatic Termination. Your rights under this License terminate
immediately if you:

(a) Fail to remit the Prosperity Contribution within 90 days of the
    Threshold being crossed;

(b) Assert a patent claim against the Foundation or any Creator
    regarding the Software; or

(c) Attempt to "closed-source" the Foundation's core components for
    exclusive private gain.

7. LIMITATION OF LIABILITY & "AS-IS" WARRANTY

7.1 Zero Liability. As the Software is provided as a public utility to
foster global innovation, the Foundation and the Creators shall not be
liable for any direct, indirect, or consequential damages (including
loss of data or business interruption) arising from the use of the code.

7.2 Warranty Disclaimer. THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS" WITHOUT
WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR IMPLIED.

8. GOVERNING LAW & GLOBAL JURISDICTION

8.1 Singapore Law. This Agreement is governed by the laws of the
Republic of Singapore.

8.2 International Arbitration. Any dispute regarding the calculation of
the Prosperity Contribution or the status of the Threshold shall be
referred to and finally resolved by arbitration administered by the
Singapore International Arbitration Centre (SIAC).
